#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Stop hook: nudge Claude to review its own diff like a PR before stopping

set -euo pipefail

INPUT=$(cat)
PORCELAIN=$(echo "$INPUT" | claude-changeset-guard review) || exit 0

cat >&2 <<EOF
You made these changes this session:

$PORCELAIN

Before stopping, review your own work as if it were someone else's pull request.
Read your full diff (git diff HEAD) and look for: bugs and unhandled edge cases,
leftover debugging or scaffolding, unclear names, and anything that violates this
repo's conventions.

Keep this tightly scoped: only fix issues within the change you already made. Do
not expand scope, refactor unrelated code, or start new work. If you spot
something out of scope, leave it or note it rather than fixing it now. When the
diff is correct and consistent on its own terms, decide it's fine, change nothing,
and stop.
EOF
exit 2
